Brunswick Corp said its first-quartersales and profits hit records despite an after-tax charge ofabout 10 mln dlrs from its new boat-building units.    The 10 mln dlrs charge, or 22 cts a share, was foramortization of intangible assets at Bayliner and Sea Ray, twoboatmakers acquired in December, a spokesman told Reuters.    Earlier it said net profits for the period were 34.7 mln or78 cts a share versus 23.8 mln or 57 cts a share a year ago.Its Mercury unit's first-quarter sales increased 26 pct andoperating earnings rose 19 pct, while its industrial productsunit operated at a slight loss, it said. Reuter&#3;